\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 A gap was closing quickly between a string of buses on one side of the road and a drifting cow on the other. Mr. Sashi Menon had to decide if his Maruti could make it through. The horn did not seem to bother either so Mr. Menon decided to make a dash for it. Prashanth gulped a large quantity of air; his fingers found their way through the ripped car seat and were tugging at the foam under. Mr. Menon, firmly depressing the horn with one palm, the accelerator with one leg, and bellowing a long curse in Malayalam, made it through the two obstinate road-users with no casualties except for a gentle smack that the Maruti bestowed on the cow's hind. Prashanth let out a loud sigh. He knew that his father would have several more such challenges to overcome before their Maruti could enter the Bangalore Airport.
\f1\fs24 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl280
\cf2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl480

\f0\fs26 \cf2 Mr. Menon was very aware of the challenges and his body responded; his eyes squinted through his glasses, dividing his forehead along four deep creases; the hair on his ears and nose sprung out, whisker-like, trying to act as antennae for additional input; his forehead divided itself along 4 deep creases; his face moved closer and closer to the windshield, pulling with it his bum to the edge of the seat; and his tongue churned out constant Malayali non-pleasantry chatter.
\f1\fs24 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl280
\cf2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl480

\f0\fs26 \cf2 Mr. Menon noticed Prashanth staring at him, and directed some of the non-pleasantries at his son. Prashanth quickly turned and continued negotiating right-of-way with other motorists, cart-pushers, pedestrians, cows and dogs.
\f1\fs24 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl280
\cf2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl480

\f0\fs26 \cf2 \'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0When the cursing subsided, Prashanth looked back at his father. He tried to picture a younger Mr. Menon, one that had his wits and hair about him. A smile was slowly forming on Prashanth\'92s face as he dressed up the mental image of Mr. Menon-of-the-early-70s in a tight brown shirt with brown bell-bottom pants and an over-sized belt buckle on a brown belt. He added extra large brown sun glasses and un-hooked the first three buttons of the shirt to reveal a newly formed tuft of hair entangled in a shining gold chain. The smile broadened to a grin when he gave the image two large triangular side-burns covering both cheeks. When the image started doing a pelvic thrust in time with an Elvis tune, he let out a muted shriek, which he quickly camouflaged with forced coughs.
\f1\fs24 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl280
\cf2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl480

\f0\fs26 \cf2  \'a0\'a0\'a0"Pull your window up. The rain is pouring in and you're catching a damn cold!" Mr. Menon snapped.
\f1\fs24 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl280
\cf2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl480

\f0\fs26 \cf2 \'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0"Yes pa." Prashanth reluctantly wound the glass up but not all the way up. He knew that he could not afford to deprive his father of any available sensory assistance, especially with visual assistance already compromised by the torrent of rain assaulting the wiper-less windshield.
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs26 \'a0
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs26 \'a0\'a0\'a0Apart from occasional opportunistic dashes through gaps in the road, the Maruti was creeping slowly through the dark wet roads. The tall street lights lining Airport Road were rendered impotent by the storm that had knocked out power supply in the area. They swayed gently with the winds and looked blindly down at the chaos that the rains had infected on the road-users. Occasional lightning strikes revealed miniature cars and buses thrashing about, jostling for pieces of the road, winning some here and conceding some there.
\f1\fs24 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl280
\cf2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl480

\f0\fs26 \cf2  \'a0\'a0\'a0Prashanth would later reflect on this exact moment in time, conjuring up the sounds of the thunder and winds, the flashes of lightning and the unrelenting rain and would think to himself how appropriately the Gods of the heavens had announced the impending chain of events that would change his life forever.
\f1\fs24 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl280
\cf2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl480

\f0\fs26 \cf2  \'a0\'a0\'a0Prashanth\'92s phone began to ring, much to the driver\'92s annoyance. For someone who worked the keyboard with such ease, Prashanth had surprisingly clumsy fingers. After a minute of fumbling around in his pocket, which the caller must have anticipated because the ringing Spiderman theme did not relent, he answered the phone.
\f1\fs24 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl280
\cf2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl480

