\pard\pardeftab720\sl280
\cf2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl480

\f0\fs26 \cf2 \'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0"You don't have enough experience to drive in this weather."
\f1\fs24 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl280
\cf2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl480

\f0\fs26 \cf2 \'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0"Pa but you've taught me so well," Prashanth said, appealing to his father's ego.
\f1\fs24 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl280
\cf2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl480

\f0\fs26 \cf2 \'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0"No da. Some other day."
\f1\fs24 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl280
\cf2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl480

\f0\fs26 \cf2 \'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0"Pleeease pa, you keep saying I need to challenge myself" he pleaded. Mr. Menon did not answer for a few minutes but Prashanth was used to that. "I'll drive very carefully pa. I think it will be a good learning experience for me," Prashanth lied, having gained most of his driving experience from their driver. Another few minutes passed. A motorist was told in Malayalam that he was an idiot.
\f1\fs24 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl280
\cf2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl480

\f0\fs26 \cf2  \'a0\'a0\'a0"Drive very carefully okay? And remember everything I taught you." Mr. Menon was of course very relieved that he did not have to drive. "But don't tell Amma anything okay? She will unnecessarily get upset."
\f1\fs24 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl280
\cf2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl480

\f0\fs26 \cf2 \'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0"Yes pa." Mr. Menon pulled up on the side of the road, and father and son exchanged places.
\f1\fs24 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl280
\cf2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl480

\f0\fs26 \cf2  \'a0\'a0\'a0"This will build character, not sitting in front of that useless computer twenty-four hours a day. You remember which one is the clutch and which one is the accelerator?"
\f1\fs24 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl280
\cf2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl480

\f0\fs26 \cf2 \'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0"Yes pa."
\f1\fs24 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl280
\cf2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl480

\f0\fs26 \cf2 \'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0The relieved Maruti, having been subjected to jerky starts and stops, now smoothly sailed through the watery roads. Mr. Menon was pleasantly surprised at his son's skill, but lest he get complacent, he continued to bark at him, warning him of the rubbish bin on the side of the road ahead (which Prashanth could see was in fact a parked car), shouting at him for driving too close to another car, driving too fast and occasionally too slow.
\f1\fs24 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl280
\cf2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl480

\f0\fs26 \cf2  \'a0\'a0\'a0"You'll break my gear box!" he growled when Prashanth changed gears "roughly". But Prashanth knew it was going well.
