\f0\fs26 \cf2  \'a0\'a0\'a0"
\i Anita will kill me if she finds out that Prashanth drove
\i0 ," Mr. Menon thought to himself. He physically shook the thought off and with it the umbrella before walking into the arrival terminal and heading towards his usual row of seats. Prashanth knew the drill; he had been to the airport many times with his father. He was carrying under his armpit a white cardboard sheet on which he had written "Welcome to Bangalore Ben & Cathy -- the Menons". He headed straight for the coffee counter. He bought two piping hot coffees and started walking to where his dad would be seated. As he approached his father, he looked up but was not prepared for what he was about to see.
\f1\fs24 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl280
\cf2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl480

\f0\fs26 \cf2 \'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0His hands went into a frenzy sending the coffee airborne. When the hot coffee came down, the rest of his body went into a frenzy and a loud muted shrill announced the minor burns. He had looked up to see his all-time super-star cricket batting hero, Rahul Dravid, sitting next to his father, not in two dimensions as he did every morning behind his room door, but in three, in flesh!
