\pard\pardeftab720\sl280
\cf2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl480

\f0\fs26 \cf2  \'a0\'a0\'a0Mr. Menon was glaring at his clumsy son. His jaws were tightly clenched shut, and his lips had parted just enough to reveal teeth and gums in a display of primitive threat. Prashanth took a step forward but turned around and walked to the bathroom. He splashed water over his face and stared at himself in the mirror, willing his throbbing temples to slow down. After what seemed like forever, he gained control of his heart rate, and started focusing on treating his reddening skin with cold water.
\f1\fs24 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl280
\cf2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl480

\f0\fs26 \cf2  \'a0\'a0\'a0When he walked back, Mr. Dravid was still there. Mr. Menon saw his son approaching and pointed to the coffee counter. Prashanth turned back and quickly brought two more coffees.
